Get on--------------------------------------------------
Imagine:---
I have got on with Sony and Bachha, but Sony is not getting on well on Lotus Notes.
Hindi Meaning:---
to get friendly relationship, 
If you say how someone is getting on, you are saying how much success they are having with what they are trying to do. (see the difference with 'come on' here)
Sentences:---
Livy's getting on very well in Russian. She learns very quickly...
Lexicon!:---
2, 4, 5
Check Out:---
